S, and Richard claps harder.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 C'mon, Sam. Make him swing like that again and you've got him.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Richard turns as a young PLAYER taps him on the shoulder.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 PLAYER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Think we can do it, coach?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I hope so. You boys deserve your first win the way you've played.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Sam winds up and pitches. The batter swings and CRACK! \par Richard's eyes follow the arc of the ball as it heads into right field.\par LEO WINN, the smallest player on the team, backpedals towards the fence.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD}{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040  (CONT'D)}{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s5\fi-140\ri4320\li4320 (to himself)\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 C'mon Leo, just like in practice. There's nothing to it, nothing at all. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 CHEERS from the crowd mount, as Leo looks up and shields his face from the sun. He tentatively raises his glove and the ball plops inside. \par A ROAR erupts from the dugout, as the players hi-five each other.\par Still moving backwards, Leo trips and falls to the ground, the ball rolling idly from his glove.\par The stunned crowd looks on in silence.\par Then the fans of "Glen's Plumbing and Heating" slowly begin to cheer as the batter rounds the bases and tags home.\par The "Pine Tree Rotary" players sit down on the bench, grumbling to themselves. Sam plops down in the middle of the mound and buries his head in his hands.\par At the scoreboard, Olivia, erases the 0 next to "Glen's Plumbing & Heating" and writes a 2. She shakes her head, throws the chalk on the ground and walks away.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f64\fs24\sl220\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 EXT. baseball field parking lot - DUSK\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Richard, Sam and Olivia walk towards their car. Richard has one arm draped over Sam's shoulder and the other around Olivia's.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Olivia\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Sam, that was your best game ever! They only got that one hit, and I scored it as an error.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Sam\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Yeah, I know. I was there, remember? What difference does it make? We still lost. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Richard pulls his son into a hug.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Richard\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 You did well, son. You all did -- even Leo.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Sam\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Aw Dad, he's no good. He lost the game for us. He always plays like that. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 He's not as good as you, but he's still out there trying his hardest and not giving up. That counts for something.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Sam shrugs off his dad's embrace and hangs his head, walking several steps behind Richard and Olivia. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 OLIVIA\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Hey look. The other team is going out for ice cream. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Across the parking lot, the other team is laughing and joking around as they pile into two minivans.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 We can go, too, if you want. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 SaM\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Dad... Let's just go home. They're going for ice cream because they won. Losers don't deserve ice cream. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 C'mon, Sam. Don't you think...\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Richard turns his head to the sound of commotion near the dumpster. He hands his car keys to Sam, while still looking in the direction of the dumpster. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD (cont'd)}{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040  (cont'd}{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 )\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Here. Get in the car. I'll be right there.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 As Richard approaches the dumpster, he hears a loud voice. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 MAN (O.C.)\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 How the hell did you drop it? What are you, stupid? It was an easy out!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 GEORGE WINN grips Leo by his t-shirt and violently shakes him back and forth. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RicHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Hey George - lighten up. It's just a game. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Surprised, George turns to face Richard. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 GEORGE\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Huh?!?! What did you say?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RiCHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 George, c'mon. Your kid did all right. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 George releases Leo, who immediately runs to grab his hat off the ground. George steps towards Richard and glares at him. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 GEORGE\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 You looking for trouble... }{\pard\plain \ql \ul\sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Dick}{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 ?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Richard backs away.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RiCHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 No. I'm just saying that your kid's not a bad player. He's a trooper. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 George stabs a finger in Richard's chest. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 GEORGE\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 No. He ain't no trooper. He's a loser. Back off, writer man. Unless you want to settle this right now. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 A horn HONKS. Richard turns to see his kids waving at him to hurry up.\par A door slams as Leo climbs into the truck. Richard takes another step back without turning his back to George.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 No, I don't want to settle this here. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 GEORGE\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Good. So why don't you go back to your kiddie books and leave us the hell alone? \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 As Richard walks to his car, the Winn's truck zooms by, brushing against him. He stops to watch the truck leave the parking lot.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f64\fs24\sl220\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 INT. KITCHEN, dow home - NIGHT\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 CARLA DOW, mid 30s, opens the oven, pulls out a casserole and places it on the stove. \par Richard walks over to the stove and stands behind Carla. He wraps his arms around her and kisses her on the neck. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Carla\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 That feels nice. So besides losing, how was the game?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 RICHARD\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Couldn't have gone better. Sam got three strikeouts. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Olivia enters the kitchen and sits down at the table.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 OLIVIA\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Daddy almost got into a fight today. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Carla turns and looks sharply at Richard.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\sl220\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 CARLA\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f64\fs24\sl220\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 He did?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f64\fs24\s